And it might save you if you could lead a raid but you can't even do that. 15 people under 56 with mediocre gear do not constitute a Fear Raid, and yet I was willing to hang around and help you guys out because I knew you didn't have enough people and every person would count. At that moment I could have called in two clerics over 52 and 60 Enchanter to help out on what became a four hour CR where some of my friends couldn't even get rez's for their deaths. The sad part is it's not the first time I've seen it happen, CoS does it all the time.<br>
<br>
You should be ashamed of yourself for the way you treat your fellow man. The dozens of people you've treated like dirt. Your &quot;friends&quot; whom you willingly lead to their deaths knowing they couldn't possibly succeed but not caring either. Or you SHOULD know. Maybe the problem is you just don't know squat about raiding and are willing to sacrifice your guild in the name of that ignorance. <br>
<br>
Yes, Poppa Cappo, I am VERY ANGRY at you. I detest what you are and what you do to people. I have every right to flame you for what I've seen you do, and anyone who says otherwise can start your own Flame thread labeled &quot;Against the Virtue of Courage&quot;<br>
<br>
Oh, and there is no such thing as a CoS PoF raid. There's only CoS PoF CR. I would know first hand. Even raids that go well have so many wipeouts that you should get laughed at. That's what you get for using a 54 as your main tank when you have higher. I'm sorry for every good deed I have done you Poppa, because you have repaid me and so many others tenfold in treachery!<br>
<br>
